## Why This Is Asked
This question tests practical design of a privacy-conscious, end-to-end streaming pipeline that validates, masks, deduplicates, and persists data with observability.

## Key Concepts
- Kinesis Data Streams, Lambda, DynamoDB dedup, S3 Parquet storage, DLQ
- JSON schema validation, field-level masking of PII, correlationId
- Backfill strategy, LocalStack testing, basic observability (CloudWatch, X-Ray)

## Code Example
```javascript
function maskPII(record) {
  const r = {...record};
  if (r.email) r.email = r.email.replace(/[^@]+@/, '***@');
  if (r.phone) r.phone = r.phone.length > 4 ? r.phone.slice(0, 3) + '****' + r.phone.slice(-4) : r.phone;
  if (r.ssn) r.ssn = '***-**-' + r.ssn.slice(-4);
  return r;
}
```

